SH.MED.BEDS.ZS-healthSystems.def: Hospital beds include inpatient beds available in public, private, general, and specialized hospitals and rehabilitation centers. In most cases beds for both acute and chronic care are included.
SH.MED.BEDS.ZS-healthSystems.name: Hospital beds
SH.MED.BEDS.ZS-healthSystems.source: Data are from the World Health Organization, supplemented by country data.

SH.MED.CMHW.P3-healthSystems.def: Community health workers include various types of community health aides, many with country-specific occupational titles such as community health officers, community health-education workers, family health workers, lady health visitors and health extension package workers.
SH.MED.CMHW.P3-healthSystems.name: Community health workers
SH.MED.CMHW.P3-healthSystems.source: World Health Organization's Global Health Workforce Statistics, OECD, supplemented by country data.

SH.MED.NUMW.P3-healthSystems.def: Nurses and midwives include professional nurses, professional midwives, auxiliary nurses, auxiliary midwives, enrolled nurses, enrolled midwives and other associated personnel, such as dental nurses and primary care nurses.
SH.MED.NUMW.P3-healthSystems.name: Nurses and midwives
SH.MED.NUMW.P3-healthSystems.source: World Health Organization's Global Health Workforce Statistics, OECD, supplemented by country data.

SH.MED.PHYS.ZS-healthSystems.def: Physicians include generalist and specialist medical practitioners.
SH.MED.PHYS.ZS-healthSystems.name: Physicians
SH.MED.PHYS.ZS-healthSystems.source: World Health Organization's Global Health Workforce Statistics, OECD, supplemented by country data.

SH.MED.SAOP.P5-healthSystems.def: Specialist surgical workforce is the number of specialist surgical, anaesthetic, and obstetric (SAO) providers who are working in each country per 100,000 population.
SH.MED.SAOP.P5-healthSystems.name: Specialist surgical workforce
SH.MED.SAOP.P5-healthSystems.source: Data collected by the Lancet Commission on Global Surgery (www.lancetglobalsurgery.org); Data collected by WHO Collaborating Centre for Surgery and Public Health at Lund University from various sources including Ministries of Health or equivalent national regulatory bodies, national official entities such as medical councils, Eurostat, OECD, WHO Euro Health For All Database, WHO EURO Technical resources for health Database; BMJ Glob Health.

SH.SGR.PROC.P5-healthSystems.def: The number of procedures undertaken in an operating theatre per 100,000 population per year in each country. A procedure is defined as the incision, excision, or manipulation of tissue that needs regional or general anaesthesia, or profound sedation to control pain.
SH.SGR.PROC.P5-healthSystems.name: Number of surgical procedures
SH.SGR.PROC.P5-healthSystems.source: The Lancet Commission on Global Surgery (www.lancetglobalsurgery.org).

SH.XPD.CHEX.GD.ZS-healthSystems.def: Level of current health expenditure expressed as a percentage of GDP.  Estimates of current health expenditures include healthcare goods and services consumed during each year. This indicator does not include capital health expenditures such as buildings, machinery, IT and stocks of vaccines for emergency or outbreaks.
SH.XPD.CHEX.GD.ZS-healthSystems.name: Current health expenditure
SH.XPD.CHEX.GD.ZS-healthSystems.source: World Health Organization Global Health Expenditure database (http://apps.who.int/nha/database).

SH.XPD.CHEX.PC.CD-healthSystems.def: Current expenditures on health per capita in current US dollars. Estimates of current health expenditures include healthcare goods and services consumed during each year.
SH.XPD.CHEX.PC.CD-healthSystems.name: Current health expenditure per capita
SH.XPD.CHEX.PC.CD-healthSystems.source: World Health Organization Global Health Expenditure database (http://apps.who.int/nha/database).

SH.XPD.CHEX.PP.CD-healthSystems.def: Current expenditures on health per capita expressed in international dollars at purchasing power parity (PPP time series based on ICP2011 PPP).
SH.XPD.CHEX.PP.CD-healthSystems.name: Current health expenditure per capita
SH.XPD.CHEX.PP.CD-healthSystems.source: World Health Organization Global Health Expenditure database (http://apps.who.int/nha/database).

SH.XPD.EHEX.CH.ZS-healthSystems.def: Share of current health expenditures funded from external sources. External sources compose of direct foreign transfers and foreign transfers distributed by government encompassing all financial inflows into the national health system from outside the country. External sources either flow through the government scheme or are channeled through non-governmental organizations or other schemes.
SH.XPD.EHEX.CH.ZS-healthSystems.name: External health expenditure
SH.XPD.EHEX.CH.ZS-healthSystems.source: World Health Organization Global Health Expenditure database (http://apps.who.int/nha/database).

SH.XPD.EHEX.PC.CD-healthSystems.def: Current external expenditures on health per capita expressed in current US dollars. External sources are composed of direct foreign transfers and foreign transfers distributed by government encompassing all financial inflows into the national health system from outside the country.
SH.XPD.EHEX.PC.CD-healthSystems.name: External health expenditure per capita
SH.XPD.EHEX.PC.CD-healthSystems.source: World Health Organization Global Health Expenditure database (http://apps.who.int/nha/database).

SH.XPD.EHEX.PP.CD-healthSystems.def: Current external expenditures on health per capita expressed in international dollars at purchasing power parity (PPP time series based on ICP2011 PPP). External sources are composed of direct foreign transfers and foreign transfers distributed by government encompassing all financial inflows into the national health system from outside the country.
SH.XPD.EHEX.PP.CD-healthSystems.name: External health expenditure per capita
SH.XPD.EHEX.PP.CD-healthSystems.source: World Health Organization Global Health Expenditure database (http://apps.who.int/nha/database).

SH.XPD.GHED.CH.ZS-healthSystems.def: Share of current health expenditures funded from domestic public sources for health.  Domestic public sources include domestic revenue as internal transfers and grants, transfers, subsidies to voluntary health insurance beneficiaries, non-profit institutions serving households (NPISH) or enterprise financing schemes as well as compulsory prepayment and social health insurance contributions. They do not include external resources spent by governments on health.
SH.XPD.GHED.CH.ZS-healthSystems.name: Domestic general government health expenditure
SH.XPD.GHED.CH.ZS-healthSystems.source: World Health Organization Global Health Expenditure database (http://apps.who.int/nha/database).

SH.XPD.GHED.GD.ZS-healthSystems.def: Public expenditure on health from domestic sources as a share of the economy as measured by GDP.
SH.XPD.GHED.GD.ZS-healthSystems.name: Domestic general government health expenditure
SH.XPD.GHED.GD.ZS-healthSystems.source: World Health Organization Global Health Expenditure database (http://apps.who.int/nha/database).

SH.XPD.GHED.GE.ZS-healthSystems.def: Public expenditure on health from domestic sources as a share of total public expenditure.  It indicates the priority of the government to spend on health from own domestic public resources.
SH.XPD.GHED.GE.ZS-healthSystems.name: Domestic general government health expenditure
SH.XPD.GHED.GE.ZS-healthSystems.source: World Health Organization Global Health Expenditure database (http://apps.who.int/nha/database).

SH.XPD.GHED.PC.CD-healthSystems.def: Public expenditure on health from domestic sources per capita expressed in current US dollars.
SH.XPD.GHED.PC.CD-healthSystems.name: Domestic general government health expenditure per capita
SH.XPD.GHED.PC.CD-healthSystems.source: World Health Organization Global Health Expenditure database (http://apps.who.int/nha/database).

SH.XPD.GHED.PP.CD-healthSystems.def: Public expenditure on health from domestic sources per capita expressed in international dollars at purchasing power parity (PPP time series based on ICP2011 PPP).
SH.XPD.GHED.PP.CD-healthSystems.name: Domestic general government health expenditure per capita
SH.XPD.GHED.PP.CD-healthSystems.source: World Health Organization Global Health Expenditure database (http://apps.who.int/nha/database).

SH.XPD.OOPC.CH.ZS-healthSystems.def: Share of out-of-pocket payments of total current health expenditures.  Out-of-pocket payments are spending on health directly out-of-pocket by households.
SH.XPD.OOPC.CH.ZS-healthSystems.name: Out-of-pocket expenditure
SH.XPD.OOPC.CH.ZS-healthSystems.source: World Health Organization Global Health Expenditure database (http://apps.who.int/nha/database).

SH.XPD.OOPC.PC.CD-healthSystems.def: Health expenditure through out-of-pocket payments per capita in USD.  Out of pocket payments are spending on health directly out of pocket by households in each country.
SH.XPD.OOPC.PC.CD-healthSystems.name: Out-of-pocket expenditure per capita
SH.XPD.OOPC.PC.CD-healthSystems.source: World Health Organization Global Health Expenditure database (http://apps.who.int/nha/database).

SH.XPD.OOPC.PP.CD-healthSystems.def: Health expenditure through out-of-pocket payments per capita in international dollars at purchasing power parity (PPP time series based on ICP2011 PPP).
SH.XPD.OOPC.PP.CD-healthSystems.name: Out-of-pocket expenditure per capita
SH.XPD.OOPC.PP.CD-healthSystems.source: World Health Organization Global Health Expenditure database (http://apps.who.int/nha/database).

SH.XPD.PVTD.CH.ZS-healthSystems.def: Share of current health expenditures funded from domestic private sources.  Domestic private sources include funds from households, corporations and non-profit organizations. Such expenditures can be either prepaid to voluntary health insurance or paid directly to healthcare providers.
SH.XPD.PVTD.CH.ZS-healthSystems.name: Domestic private health expenditure
SH.XPD.PVTD.CH.ZS-healthSystems.source: World Health Organization Global Health Expenditure database (http://apps.who.int/nha/database).

SH.XPD.PVTD.PC.CD-healthSystems.def: Current private expenditures on health per capita expressed in current US dollars. Domestic private sources include funds from households, corporations and non-profit organizations. Such expenditures can be either prepaid to voluntary health insurance or paid directly to healthcare providers.
SH.XPD.PVTD.PC.CD-healthSystems.name: Domestic private health expenditure per capita
SH.XPD.PVTD.PC.CD-healthSystems.source: World Health Organization Global Health Expenditure database (http://apps.who.int/nha/database).

SH.XPD.PVTD.PP.CD-healthSystems.def: Current private expenditures on health per capita expressed in international dollars at purchasing power parity (PPP time series based on ICP2011 PPP).
SH.XPD.PVTD.PP.CD-healthSystems.name: Domestic private health expenditure per capita
SH.XPD.PVTD.PP.CD-healthSystems.source: World Health Organization Global Health Expenditure database (http://apps.who.int/nha/database).
